Being married to a teacher there is one vital part that's being left out. This needs to be a rare exception, not the rule on assignment submissions. 

&amp;#x200B;

If you turn in every assignment on time and make a good faith effort then life happens once, it's going to get some leeway. If every assignment can't be completed on time, you really are just planning and allocating your time poorly then expecting the teacher to compensate for it.

If you're an adult, also do this. 

&amp;#x200B;

In the law, it's actually codified into different standards if you ask for more time before a deadline as opposed to after.  BAsically, a very liberal standard if you ask before, and higher standards like good cause, excusable neglect, etc if you ask after.
